00:00:22.668 --> 00:00:28.200
What are you cooking, Mrs. Uma?
Chicken With Chickpea Curry (Chana Chicken)

00:00:31.603 --> 00:00:34.171
Ingredients required to make Chicken With Chickpea

00:00:34.397 --> 00:00:40.854
Chicken, Soaked Bengal Gram(Chickpea), Tamarind, Ginger-Garlic Paste, Salt, Red Chilli Powder

00:00:41.163 --> 00:00:47.993
Green Chilli, Curry Leaves, Onions &amp; Coriander Leaves Paste, Small Onions &amp; Garam Masala

00:00:51.059 --> 00:00:56.450
Take a pan and heat some oil

00:00:59.952 --> 00:01:08.085
Soak the small onions and the bengal gram in water prior to cooking

00:01:10.633 --> 00:01:14.869
Add the peeled small onions into the pan

00:01:17.628 --> 00:01:21.627
Fry them till they're a nice golden brown

00:01:46.735 --> 00:01:48.911
Keep the fried onions aside

00:02:03.120 --> 00:02:09.242
Add the onions and coriander leaves' paste into the pan

00:02:16.650 --> 00:02:22.936
Take some garam masala powder with coriander seeds,
cinnamon, cloves, cardamom and cumin seeds

00:02:26.997 --> 00:02:32.500
Grind all these into a powder and add it into the pan

00:02:37.625 --> 00:02:40.460
Now, add the chicken, 250 gms

00:02:47.348 --> 00:02:57.962
Add some salt for taste, a little turmeric powder and red chilli powder

00:03:12.161 --> 00:03:16.898
Add two spoons of ginger-garlic paste

00:03:22.461 --> 00:03:32.097
Add some curry leaves and green chillies according to taste

00:03:34.689 --> 00:03:39.353
Add a little water and let it simmer for 2 - 3 minutes

00:03:56.924 --> 00:04:03.341
Now, add a cup of soaked bengal gram

00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:38.255
Add the fried small onions

00:04:44.069 --> 00:04:51.666
Add a little tamarind juice

00:04:58.481 --> 00:05:06.038
Close the lid and cook for about 7 - 10 minutes

00:05:10.958 --> 00:05:13.326
Serve it in a bowl

